        <bioghist id="ref4">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Lydia Maria Child, born in Medford, Massachusetts in 1802, published on numerous subjects, including domestic advice, children's literature, abolition and religion, and was an active abolitionist in New York and Massachusetts. She died in 1880.</p>
        </bioghist>
